  "description": "The amalgamation of two flats to create a 4-bedroom larger family unit; demolition of existing first floor rear extension (and external stairs); excavation at basement level including front and rear lightwell; erection of ground floor rear extension; and replacement first floor rear extension with roof terrace",
  "title_number": [
    "LN116724"
  ],
  "site_number": "133",
  "lapsed_date": "23/12/2024",
  "lpa_name": "Hackney",
  "uprn": "100021063334",
  "appeal_status": null,
  "decision_conditions": [
    "<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-d3998408-7fff-49c3-166b-1da3c21e06aa\"><br><span style=\"font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\">The proposed roof terrace at first floor level, by reason of its size, design and position, would result in loss of privacy and overlooking to neighbouring windows and their amenity space that would result in an an unacceptable adverse impact on the amenity of the neighbouring occupiers particularly 135 Osbaldeston Road. As such the proposed development is contrary to policy D1 (London’s form, character and capacity for growth) of the London Plan (2021), policy LP2 (Development and amenity) of the Hackney Local Plan (2020) and the guidance contained within Hackney Residential Extensions and Alterations </span><span style=\"font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\">Supplementary Planning Document</span><span style=\"font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"> (2009).</span></span><br></p>",
    "<p><span id=\"docs-internal-guid-ce86df65-7fff-936f-c3bb-6c2d0d746e5a\"><span style=\"font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\">The proposed roof terrace by reason of its design, scale and position would result in the introduction of an incongruous addition that fails to respect the character and appearance of the subject building or wider terrace, contrary to&nbsp; policies D3 (Optimising site capacity through the design-led approach), D4 (Delivering good design), </span><span style=\"font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\">HC1 Heritage conservation and growth</span><span style=\"font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\"> of the London Plan (2021) and Policy LP1 (Design Quality and Local Character) and LP3 (Designated Heritage Asset) of the Hackney Local Plan (2020) the relevant sections of the </span><span style=\"font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline;\">Residential Extensions and Alterations Supplementary Planning Document (2009) Northwold and Cazenove Conservation Area Character Appraisal (2010).</span></span><br></p>"
  ],
